The `Bus` class has three methods: `disembark`, `board`, and `drive`. The `disembark` method randomly removes passengers from the bus based on the disembark probability distribution. The `board` method checks if any passengers are waiting at the current stop and adds them to the bus with a probability of `boarding_probability`. The `drive` method simply prints a message saying that the bus is driving to the next stop.

